{
  "texts": [
    "To identify at-risk students, Huang et al (2022) suggested using LSTM network techniques.",
    "The method involved extracting behavioral data from a public dataset, and creating two datasets including sequential datasets and aggregated datasets.",
    "In addition to LSTM, eight ML techniques were used to train the prediction models on these datasets.",
    "According to the findings, the models trained on sequential datasets using LSTM achieved 84% accuracy, which was higher than that of other ML techniques.",
    "The limitations of the study include that even though the experiment has only used data from one course, neither the raw log data was not included, nor the learning behaviors sequence features were not extracted."
  ]
}